It should be used to create variables (e.g. to initalize filters).""" self.inlet_diameter = self.parent.venturi.inlet_diameter * 25.4 self.throat_diameter = self.parent.venturi.throat_diameter * 25.4 self.throat_area = math.pi * (self.throat_diameter / 2000) ** 2 self.beta = self.throat_diameter/self.inlet_diameter self.initial_cd = 0.98 def update(self,counter): """This function is called once per lab clock (100mS). The value it returns becomes the parameter's value.""" try: lab = self.parent.parent.parent venturi = self.parent.venturi try: self.ap = venturi.absolute_pressure.value * 1000 #In Pa except TypeError: return None #channel not ready self.dp = venturi.differential_pressure T = venturi.temperature #In Kelvin MW_Air = 0.02896559 #kg/mol MW_H2O = 0.01801528 #kg/mol k = 1.399 Z = 1 Rconst = 8.3144 T_0 = 273.11 mu_0 = 0.000017894 S = 110.56 P_Standard = 101325 T_Standard = 293.15 if self.cd.value is None or math.isnan(self.cd.value) or math.isinf(self.cd.value): self.cd.update(self.initial_cd) x_H2O = cfr.part1065.x_H2O_Dewpoint(lab.ambient.dewpoint.value + 273.15,lab.ambient.pressure.value) MW_Mix = (MW_Air * (1 - x_H2O) + MW_H2O * x_H2O) * 1000 r = 1 - self.dp/self.ap Cf_i = ((2 * k * (r ** ((k - 1) / k) - 1)) / ((k - 1) * (self.beta ** 4 - r ** (-2 / k)))) ** 0.5 N_i = self.cd * Cf_i * self.throat_area * self.ap / (Z * MW_Mix / 1000 * Rconst * T) ** 0.5 #mol/s
mu_i = mu_0 * ((T / T_0) ** 1.5) * (T_0 + S) / (T + S) Qm_i = N_i * MW_Mix / 1000 #kg/s rho_i = P_Standard * MW_Mix / (Rconst * T_Standard) / 1000 #kg/m^3 Qs_i_std = Qm_i / rho_i #m^3/s self.re.update(4 * MW_Mix / 1000 * N_i / (math.pi * (self.throat_diameter / 1000) * mu_i)) self.cd.update(venturi.polynomial.apply(self.re.value)) self.traditional.update(Qs_i_std / 0.3048 ** 3 * 60) #scfm return N_i except RuntimeError: #(TypeError,ValueError,AttributeError): # Calculations fail when the tunnel is off # this statement prevents the alarm self.re = None self.cd = None return None
